{"title":"The Disciples","link":"https://kottke.org/24/08/the-disciples","date":1724086241000,"content":"\n        <p>For his project <a href=\"https://www.jamesmollison.com/the-disciples\">The Disciples</a>, photographer James Mollison took photo montages of fans outside of music concerts. See if you can guess which concerts these groups of fans attended:</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/disciples-01.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/disciples-01.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/disciples-01.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"434\" alt=\"seven people who attended a Lady Gaga concert, wearing colorful, wacky clothes\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/disciples-02.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/disciples-02.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/disciples-02.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"434\" alt=\"seven people who attended a Merle Haggard concert, wearing mostly denim\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/disciples-03.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/disciples-03.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/disciples-03.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"434\" alt=\"seven people who attended a 50 Cent concert, wearing baseball caps, baggy jeans, and big jackets\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/disciples-04.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/disciples-04.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/disciples-04.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"434\" alt=\"eight people who attended a The Casualties concert, wearing leather and mohawks\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/disciples-05.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/disciples-05.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/disciples-05.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1300\" height=\"434\" alt=\"eight people who attended a Tori Amos concert, wearing dark, muted colors\" /></p>\n\n<p>Hereâ€™s Mollison on the project:</p>\n\n<blockquote><p>Over three years I photographed fans outside different concerts. I am fascinated by the different tribes of people that attend them, and how people emulate celebrity to form their identity.</p>\n\n<p>As I photographed the project I began to see how the concerts became events for people to come together with surrogate â€˜familiesâ€™, a chance to relive their youth or try and be part of a scene that happened before they were born.</p></blockquote>\n\n<p>Fascinating! From top to bottom: Lady Gaga, Merle Haggard, 50 Cent, The Casualties, and Tori Amos. Hereâ€™s a video featuring some of the photos accompanied by music from the corresponding artists:</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p>Mollison published <a href=\"https://www.jamesmollison.com/disciples-copystand\">a book featuring the photos</a>; <a href=\"https://www.jamesmollison.com/shop/the-disciples\">a signed copy is available from his website</a>.</p>\n\n        \n\n         <p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/celebrity\">celebrity</a> Â· <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/James%20Mollison\">James Mollison</a> Â· <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/music\">music</a> Â· 